1 Transportation Cabinet and the Department of Kentucky State Police that describes:
2 (a) How to communicate with a fleet support specialist who is available during
3 the times the vehicle is in operation;
4 (b) How to safely remove the fully autonomous vehicle from the roadway and
5 steps to safely tow the vehicle;
6 (c) How to recognize whether the automated driving system is engaged on the
7 fully autonomous vehicle; and
8 (d) Any additional information the manufacturer or owner deems necessary
9 regarding hazardous conditions or public safety risks associated with the
10 operation of the fully autonomous vehicle.
11 (4) A school district shall not operate a fully autonomous vehicle as a school bus, as
12 defined in KRS 156.153, or use any fully autonomous vehicle to transport
13 students for any purpose.
14 (5) A person shall not operate a fully autonomous vehicle on the highways of this
15 state if the vehicle requires an operator with a commercial driver's license as
16 defined in KRS 281A.010.
17 Section 2. KRS 281.764 (Effective August 1, 2026) is amended to read as
18 follows:
19 (1) A motor carrier may operate a platoon on the highways of this state if the motor
20 carrier complies with this section.
21 (2) Motor carriers wishing to operate a platoon shall provide notification to the
22 department and the Kentucky State Police, including a plan for general platoon
23 operations. The department shall have thirty (30) days from the date of receipt to
24 review the notification plan submitted and determine whether it will approve or
25 reject the plan. If the department rejects a submitted plan, it shall inform the motor
26 carrier of the reason for the rejection and provide guidance on how to resubmit the
27 notification and plan to meet the standards.
